The '''Southern Management Association''' (SMA) [http://www.southernmanagement.org] is a regional affiliate of the [[Academy of Management]] [http://www.aomonline.org] and, along with [[SAGE Publications|SAGE]], publishes the [[Journal of Management]]. It is an academic association with a stated primary purpose to advance the teaching, learning, research, and practice of management. As of 2017, membership was over 1000 professors of management, doctoral students, and business executives.<ref>[http://www.southernmanagement.org/about http://www.southernmanagement.org/]</ref>

As an academic association, SMA has deemed the development and dissemination of new ideas and approaches in the science of management as a critical objective. The annual meeting hosts consortia for doctoral students, professional development workshops, paper presentations, symposia, and other sessions of attendee interest.

